@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "LineBloks" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbenchmust have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile (except on an 'Unclickable' tile) on
the board, this will rotate all 8 tiles surrounding it by one
position in a clockwise manner. If you click on a border tile, the
tiles located at the other edge of the board will rotate with the
other tiles located around the tile you clicked on. Note that when
you click on 'Bomb' or 'Lightning' tiles, the neighbouring tiles do
not rotate.

  When you move tiles around, if a row or column of 8 tiles of the
same pattern is not formed, a new tile is added to the board. Be
careful not to let the board fill up completely because when that
happens, the game is over.

  When you complete a row or column with tiles of the same pattern,
those tiles are removed from the board and you get points depending
on the number of columns or rows you have made, 1 row or column of
tiles of the same pattern will give you 10 points, 2 rows or columns
give 100 points, 3 rows or columns give 1000 points and so on...

  As you progress in the game, new tiles with different patterns
are added to the game board as well as the following tiles:

 -Bombs:             A Bomb (indicated by an 'explosion' icon) will
                     eliminate any tile that is located next to it,
                     either horizontally, vertically or diagonally.
                     Any tile removed will give you 1 point.

 -Unclickable Tiles: An Unclickable tile (indicated by a tile that
                     is 'pressed down') is just that: unclickable,
                     what this means is that nothing will happen if
                     you click on it. However, the tile itself can
                     move everywhere you like by clicking on a
                     'normal' neighbouring tile.

 -Lightning Tiles:   A Lightning tile (indicated by an 'electric
                     flash' icon), when clicked on, will generate
                     lightning bolts horizontally and vertically,
                     eliminating any tile that is located in their
                     paths. Each eliminated tile will give you 1
                     point.

 -Blocks:            Blocks do not serve any purpose other than
                     being in the way when you don't need them.
                     They can be moved anywhere you like.

  Continue the game until the board gets completely full or empty,
in both cases the game ends. If the board gets emptied, your final
score will be doubled.

  Have fun!

